item.description:
Let's walk at Wingaersheek. Note change of date and now the time is 11 am!

You can let the dogs off the leash and I usually walk the beach twice to make it a longer walk..

Situated in the western part of Gloucester on Atlantic Street off Rte. 133 and Concord Street, this beautiful beach is along the Annisquam River and Ipswich Bay.

Wingaersheek Beach has white sands, crystal clear waters, and huge rocks in the water that you can climb around at low tide. lovely views of the lighthouse and saltmarsh..
